events/strFilename: English Premier League 2020-09-12 Crystal Palace vs Southampton
events/strDescriptionEN: Crystal Palace and Southampton collide on the opening weekend of the new Premier League season. The two performed very differently after last season's restart, with Southampton one of the most in-form teams, while Palace lost seven of its last eight.

events/strFilename: English Premier League 2020-09-12 Fulham vs Arsenal
events/strDescriptionEN: Newly-promoted Fulham's Premier League adventure begins with a London derby against Arsenal at Craven Cottage. Mikel Arteta begins his first full season in charge of the Gunners and has bolstered his squad by signing Willian from Chelsea.

events/strFilename: English Premier League 2020-09-12 Liverpool vs Leeds
events/strDescriptionEN: Leeds United faces a big test on its long-awaited return to the Premier League as it takes on defending champion, Liverpool. Jurgen Klopp's men are well-rested, unlike other title contenders, as they didn't play the UEFA Champions League in August.

events/strFilename: English Premier League 2020-09-12 West Ham vs Newcastle
events/strDescriptionEN: After spending much of last season battling relegation, West Ham United and Newcastle United begin the new season in search of a fresh start. The Magpies continue life under long-term owner Mike Ashley after their proposed offseason sale fell through.

events/strFilename: English Premier League 2020-09-13 Tottenham vs Everton
events/strDescriptionEN: Two titans of world soccer collide on the opening weekend as Jose Mourinho's Tottenham Hotspur takes on Carlo Ancelotti's Everton. Spurs striker Harry Kane has an impressive record against Everton, scoring nine goals in 10 games.

events/strFilename: English Premier League 2020-09-13 West Brom vs Leicester
events/strDescriptionEN: Reigning Premier League Golden Boot winner Jamie Vardy looks to make a fast start to the season as Leicester City heads on the road to face newly-promoted West Bromwich Albion. The Foxes are aiming to build on last season's superb 5th-place finish.

events/strFilename: English Premier League 2020-09-14 Brighton vs Chelsea
events/strDescriptionEN: Graham Potter’s Brighton and Hove Albion avoided relegation last season with a steely resilience to not be beaten. Such durability was showcased against Chelsea at AMEX Stadium as Alireza Jahanbakhsh’s bicycle kick secured a point for the Seagulls.

events/strFilename: English Premier League 2020-09-14 Sheffield United vs Wolves
events/strDescriptionEN: Sheffield United and Wolverhampton Wanderers begin their season by going head-to-head at Bramall Lane. Both teams were in the hunt for European qualification for most of last season but missed out after falling away in the final couple of weeks.

events/strFilename: English Premier League 2020-09-19 Arsenal vs West Ham
events/strDescriptionEN: An all-London clash at Emirates Stadium as Arsenal hosts West Ham United. Gunners boss Mikel Arteta is looking to build on a successful first nine months in charge, which saw his team win the FA Cup and Community Shield in the last two months.

events/strFilename: English Premier League 2020-09-19 Everton vs West Brom
events/strDescriptionEN: Everton faces newly-promoted West Bromwich Albion at Goodison Park. After a disappointing 12th-place finish last season, Carlo Ancelotti will be looking to get his team back in the top half of tha table and secure a European qualification spot.

events/strFilename: English Premier League 2020-09-19 Leeds vs Fulham
English Premier League 2020-09-19 Manchester United vs Crystal Palace
events/strDescriptionEN: Manchester United gets its 2020/21 Premier League campaign underway against Crystal Palace at Old Trafford. The Red Devils have bolstered their ranks during the transfer window with the signing of Dutch midfielder Donny van de Beek.

events/strFilename: English Premier League 2020-09-20 Chelsea vs Liverpool
events/strDescriptionEN: Liverpool heads on the road to face Chelsea in the first major test of its Premier League title defence. Its trophy presentation last season took place after a gripping 5-3 victory over Chelsea, which included a goal from Christian Pulisic.

events/strFilename: English Premier League 2020-09-20 Leicester vs Burnley
events/strDescriptionEN: Burnley travels to Leicester City in the first away game of its 2020/21 Premier League campaign. Sean Dyche's team finished 10th last season and will be looking to challenge for a UEFA Europa League spot this time around.

events/strFilename: English Premier League 2020-09-20 Newcastle vs Brighton
events/strDescriptionEN: Brighton and Hove Albion makes the long trip to the north of England to face Newcastle United at St. James' Park. New signings Callum Wilson and Jeff Hendrick have hit the ground running for Newcastle, both scoring on matchday one.

events/strFilename: English Premier League 2020-09-20 Southampton vs Tottenham
events/strDescriptionEN: Southampton welcomes Jose Mourinho's Tottenham Hotspur to St Mary's Stadium. Saints fans will hope that star striker Danny Ings can replicate his form from last season, which saw him finish second in the race for the Premier League Golden Boot.

events/strFilename: English Premier League 2020-09-21 Aston Villa vs Sheffield United
events/strDescriptionEN: After securing top-flight survival on the final day, Aston Villa begins its 2020/21 Premier League campaign against Sheffield United. The Blades are seeking revenge after goal-line technology robbed Chris Wilder's team of a win at Villa Park in July.

events/strFilename: English Premier League 2020-09-21 Wolves vs Manchester City
events/strDescriptionEN: Manchester City's Premier League season finally gets underway as it takes on Wolverhampton Wanderers. City failed to beat Wolves in both matches last year, with the latter overcoming a two-goal deficit to win 3-2 in a thriller at Molineux.

events/strFilename: English Premier League 2020-09-26 Brighton vs Manchester United
events/strDescriptionEN: Ole Gunnar Solskjaer's Manchester United heads on the road for the first time this Premier League season as it takes on Brighton and Hove Albion. Instrumental midfielder Bruno Fernandes scored a brace in a 3-0 win when United last visited in June.

events/strFilename: English Premier League 2020-09-26 Burnley vs Southampton
events/strDescriptionEN: Two English strikers come up against their former teams as Danny Ings' Southampton visits Jay Rodriguez's Burnley at Turf Moor. Ings scored one of his 22 Premier League goals last season against Burnley, as the Clarets won 2-1 at St Mary's.

events/strFilename: English Premier League 2020-09-26 Crystal Palace vs Everton
events/strDescriptionEN: Crystal Palace and Everton meet at Selhurst Park in the Premier League. Everton's midfield has been revamped over the summer, with the introduction of James Rodriguez, Allan and Abdoulaye Doucoure providing a new look to Carlo Ancelotti's team.

events/strFilename: English Premier League 2020-09-26 West Brom vs Chelsea
events/strDescriptionEN: The Hawthorns opens its doors to Chelsea as West Bromwich Albion continues to readjust to life back in the Premier League. Chelsea has a strong record at this ground, winning its last three matches here.

events/strFilename: English Premier League 2020-09-27 Manchester City vs Leicester
events/strDescriptionEN: Manchester City and Leicester City meet at Etihad Stadium. Since winning 3-1 here on the way to winning the Premier League, Leicester has lost all four times it has visited, with former star Riyad Mahrez scoring in last season's 3-1 result.

events/strFilename: English Premier League 2020-09-27 Sheffield United vs Leeds
events/strDescriptionEN: Pride is on the line in this Yorkshire Derby as Sheffield United hosts Leeds United. This is the first time that these two soccer teams have met in the Premier League since 1994, although they have met 12 times in other competitions since then.

events/strFilename: English Premier League 2020-09-27 Tottenham vs Newcastle
events/strDescriptionEN: Newcastle United visits Tottenham Hotspur Stadium a year since winning 1-0 on its first visit there. Newcastle signings Callum Wilson and Ryan Fraser were linked with Tottenham Hotspur in the summer - could they inspire a win for the Magpies?

events/strFilename: English Premier League 2020-09-27 West Ham vs Wolves
events/strDescriptionEN: Three months after winning 2-0 at London Stadium, Wolverhampton Wanderers return to East London aiming for a fifth-straight win over West Ham United. Since returning to the Premier League, Wolves has not conceded once to the Hammers.

events/strFilename: English Premier League 2020-09-28 Fulham vs Aston Villa
events/strDescriptionEN: Fulham and Aston Villa clash in the Premier League for the first time in six-and-a-half years. The pair did meet in the EFL Championship playoff final at the end of the 2017/18 season, with a Tom Cairney goal sealing a 1-0 win for Fulham.

events/strFilename: English Premier League 2020-09-28 Liverpool vs Arsenal
events/strDescriptionEN: Liverpool may be the current Premier League champion but it has already lost to Arsenal once this season, as the Gunners won the season-opening Community Shield back in August. Can Liverpool get its revenge as Mikel Arteta's men come to Anfield?

events/strFilename: English Premier League 2020-10-03 Chelsea vs Crystal Palace
events/strDescriptionEN: Chelsea and Crystal Palace clash in a London derby at Stamford Bridge. The host has strengthened in almost every area of the field over the summer, while the Eagles have finally spent some of the £50m they received for Aaron Wan-Bissaka in 2019.

events/strFilename: English Premier League 2020-10-03 Everton vs Brighton
events/strDescriptionEN: Everton, which has started the season brightly under Carlo Ancelotti, takes on Brighton & Hove Albion, whose manager Graham Potter has assembled a squad many consider capable of upsetting the odds this season.

events/strFilename: English Premier League 2020-10-03 Leeds vs Manchester City
events/strDescriptionEN: For the first time in 16 years, Leeds United welcomes Manchester City to Elland Road. This matchup will see Pep Guardiola and Marcelo Bielsa - two managers who have certainly left their mark on the beautiful game and each other - go head-to-head.

events/strFilename: English Premier League 2020-10-03 Newcastle vs Burnley
events/strDescriptionEN: Newcastle United and Burnley square off at St. James' Park, where the Magpies were humbled 3-0 by Brighton and Hove Albion in their home opener. Newcastle did bounce back from that defeat by thumping Morecambe 7-0 in the Carabao Cup, though.

events/strFilename: English Premier League 2020-10-04 Arsenal vs Sheffield United
events/strDescriptionEN: Chris Wilder's Sheffield United travels to north London to take on a rejuvenated Arsenal led by Mikel Arteta. In their first season back in the Premier League, the Blades took four points off Arsenal, including a 1-1 draw at Emirates Stadium.

events/strFilename: English Premier League 2020-10-04 Aston Villa vs Liverpool
events/strDescriptionEN: Aston Villa and Liverpool square off at Villa Park, where last season, these teams produced one of the most exciting finishes of the campaign, as Liverpool scored twice late on to overturn an early Trezeguet goal.

events/strFilename: English Premier League 2020-10-04 Leicester vs West Ham
events/strDescriptionEN: Leicester City hosts West Ham United at King Power Stadium as Brendan Rodgers' team looks to continue its good start to the season. The Hammers, meanwhile, are in the middle of an intimidating run of fixtures.

events/strFilename: English Premier League 2020-10-04 Manchester United vs Tottenham
events/strDescriptionEN: Tottenham Hotspur makes the trip to Old Trafford to take on Manchester United. Spurs has only beaten United once in its last four attempts, a 3-0 win at the ‘Theatre of Dreams’ when Jose Mourinho was in the opposing dugout.

events/strFilename: English Premier League 2020-10-04 Southampton vs West Brom
events/strDescriptionEN: Southampton welcomes West Bromwich Albion back to St. Mary's for the first time since October 2017, when Sofiane Boufal scored the only goal of the game as the Saints came out on top. Just three Southampton players remain from that starting line-up.

events/strFilename: English Premier League 2020-10-04 Wolves vs Fulham
events/strDescriptionEN: Wolverhampton Wanderers does battle with Fulham, which has made a rocky start to life back in the top flight. Nuno Espirito Santo, meanwhile, has continued to bolster his side with his compatriots, meaning Wolves now has 10 Portuguese players.

events/strFilename: English Premier League 2020-10-17 Chelsea vs Southampton
events/strDescriptionEN: Chelsea resumes its Premier League campaign with the arrival of Southampton in South West London. New signing Timo Werner continues to chase his first Premier League goal for the Blues, who beat Crystal Palace 4-0 last time out.

events/strFilename: English Premier League 2020-10-17 Everton vs Liverpool
events/strDescriptionEN: Fierce rivals Everton and Liverpool meet for the second behind-closed-doors Merseyside Derby, with the Toffees flying high at the top of the table alongside the Reds. Goodison Park hosted both teams' first game of Project Restart.

events/strFilename: English Premier League 2020-10-17 Manchester City vs Arsenal
events/strDescriptionEN: Mikel Arteta returns to Manchester City, targeting another victory over his former mentor Pep Guardiola, who he knocked out of last season’s FA Cup. Arsenal, however, does not enjoy playing at Etihad Stadium, having last won here in 2015.

events/strFilename: English Premier League 2020-10-17 Newcastle vs Manchester United
events/strDescriptionEN: Steve Bruce eyes back-to-back home victories as a stuttering Manchester United visits Newcastle United. Ole Gunnar Solskjaer's team struggled at St James' Park last year, with a late Matty Longstaff goal securing an unexpected win for the Magpies.

events/strFilename: English Premier League 2020-10-18 Crystal Palace vs Brighton
events/strDescriptionEN: Crystal Palace plays Brighton and Hove Albion in the first M23 Derby of 2020. Both teams shipped four goals in their last game before the international break, though Palace has already beaten Manchester United this season.

events/strFilename: English Premier League 2020-10-18 Leicester vs Aston Villa
events/strDescriptionEN: Returning to action for the first time since stunning defending champion Liverpool 7-2, Aston Villa heads on the road to face fellow in-form team Leicester City. The Foxes have a major scalp of their own this season after beating Manchester City 5-2.

events/strFilename: English Premier League 2020-10-18 Sheffield United vs Fulham
events/strDescriptionEN: Sheffield United looks to shake off its second season syndrome as it takes on fellow struggler Fulham. The visitor has dominated this fixture in recent times, winning the last three meetings including a 5-4 victory at Bramall Lane in 2017.

events/strFilename: English Premier League 2020-10-18 Tottenham vs West Ham
events/strDescriptionEN: Tottenham Hotspur Stadium hosts a London derby as West Ham United has the unenviable task of taking on a Spurs team that humiliated Manchester United last time out. The Hammers were the first road team to beat Spurs here, though, in 2019.

events/strFilename: English Premier League 2020-10-19 Leeds vs Wolves
events/strDescriptionEN: Leeds United’s return to the Premier League has brought huge excitement, with Marcelo Bielsa producing positive results and performances. Having held Manchester City to a 1-1 draw last time out, can Leeds now see off Wolverhampton Wanderers?

events/strFilename: English Premier League 2020-10-19 West Brom vs Burnley
events/strDescriptionEN: West Bromwich Albion's return to the Premier League has been tough going so far, with just one point from its opening four matches. Can Slaven Bilic's team kickstart its season as fellow struggler Burnley comes to town?

events/strFilename: English Premier League 2020-10-23 Aston Villa vs Leeds
English Premier League 2020-10-24 Fulham vs Crystal Palace
events/strDescriptionEN: Roy Hodgson takes Crystal Palace on a short trip across London to face newly-promoted Fulham. Scott Parker's side has struggled to re-acclimatize to life in the Premier League, without a point in its first four games.

events/strFilename: English Premier League 2020-10-24 Liverpool vs Sheffield United
events/strDescriptionEN: Reigning champion Liverpool takes on a side which gave it plenty of problems last season in Sheffield United. Although Liverpool came away from these fixtures last year with six points, the Blades acquitted themselves well against the champion.

events/strFilename: English Premier League 2020-10-24 Manchester United vs Chelsea
events/strDescriptionEN: Manchester United and Chelsea square off as two of the Premier League's biggest teams go head-to-head once again. Chelsea's big-money signings are yet to start paying off, as the likes of Timo Werner struggle to adapt to the English game.

events/strFilename: English Premier League 2020-10-24 West Ham vs Manchester City
events/strDescriptionEN: Manchester City travels to the London Stadium to take on a West Ham United side which has started the season better than any of its fans could have expected. Pep Guardiola's side, meanwhile, has yet to hit top gear in the Premier League this season.

English Premier League 2021-05-02 Newcastle vs Arsenal
events/strDescriptionEN: Newcastle United hopes to stay away from the relegation zone when it hosts Arsenal. The Magpies are currently unbeaten in their last five matches at St. James’ Park, but face an Arsenal team looking to secure a European place.

events/strFilename: English Premier League 2021-05-02 Tottenham vs Sheffield United
events/strDescriptionEN: Having lost the EFL Cup final, Tottenham Hotspur resumes its league campaign with a game against already relegated Sheffield United. The Blades’ last trip to Tottenham back in 2019, was embroiled by a controversial VAR decision.

events/strFilename: English Premier League 2021-05-03 Burnley vs West Ham
English Premier League 2021-05-03 West Brom vs Wolves
English Premier League 2021-05-07 Leicester vs Newcastle
English Premier League 2021-05-08 Leeds vs Tottenham
events/strDescriptionEN: Leeds United hosts Tottenham Hotspur at Elland Road. Spurs sank Leeds 3-0 in London during the festive period, but may struggle at a stadium where Manchester United, Manchester City, Liverpool, Chelsea and Arsenal have all dropped points this season.

events/strFilename: English Premier League 2021-05-08 Liverpool vs Southampton
events/strDescriptionEN: Liverpool hosts Southampton hoping to keep alive its dwindling chances of finishing in the top four. The Saints have been woeful in 2021, winning just three times, with the first of those coming via a Danny Ings goal in the first week of the year.

events/strFilename: English Premier League 2021-05-08 Manchester City vs Chelsea
events/strDescriptionEN: Manchester City and Chelsea meet in what could be a preview of the upcoming UEFA Champions League final. The teams met last month at Wembley in the FA Cup semi-finals, with Thomas Tuchel trumping Pep Guardiola on that occasion.

events/strFilename: English Premier League 2021-05-08 Sheffield United vs Crystal Palace
events/strDescriptionEN: Can already-relegated Sheffield United salvage some pride against visiting Crystal Palace? Roy Hodgson’s sides last trip to Bramall Lane ended in a 1-0 defeat, with John Lundstram scoring the winner for the Blades.

events/strFilename: English Premier League 2021-05-09 Arsenal vs West Brom
events/strDescriptionEN: Having both endured difficult seasons, Arsenal and West Bromwich Albion meet at Emirates Stadium. Will The Gunners suffer a continental hangover from their Europa League semi-final second leg against former manager Unai Emery?

events/strFilename: English Premier League 2021-05-09 Aston Villa vs Manchester United
events/strDescriptionEN: Manchester United travels to Villa Park chasing a third-straight league win over Aston Villa. Bruno Fernandes has scored penalties in each of the two previous victories, a 3-0 win in Birmingham last season and a 2-1 triumph at Old Trafford earlier in the campaign.

events/strFilename: English Premier League 2021-05-09 West Ham vs Everton
events/strDescriptionEN: 16 years after taking Everton to the UEFA Champions League, David Moyes aims to do the same with West Ham United as the London outfit chases a top-four finish. The Hammers snatched a 1-0 victory at Goodison Park on New Years Day.

events/strFilename: English Premier League 2021-05-09 Wolves vs Brighton
events/strDescriptionEN: Wolverhampton Wanderers have been inconsistent at Molineux with just two victories in the last nine league games there. Brighton and Hove Albion head to the West Midlands relishing its road games, having won more away than at home.

events/strFilename: English Premier League 2021-05-10 Fulham vs Burnley
events/strDescriptionEN: Relegation to the EFL Championship is almost a certainty when Fulham welcomes Burnley to Craven Cottage. These two teams couldn’t be separated earlier in the season, playing out a 1-1 draw in the reverse fixture at Turf Moor.

events/strFilename: English Premier League 2021-05-11 Southampton vs Crystal Palace
events/strDescriptionEN: Two teams in the bottom half of the Premier League table go head-to-head as Southampton hosts Crystal Palace. These sides should be safe from relegation, but will want to pick up as many points as possible to end their season on a high.

events/strFilename: English Premier League 2021-05-11 Manchester United vs Leicester
events/strDescriptionEN: Manchester United hosts Leicester City in a top-four clash between two clubs with more to play for outside of the Premier League than within it, as both sides are still in with a chance of lifting trophies in other competitions.

events/strFilename: English Premier League 2021-05-12 Chelsea vs Arsenal
events/strDescriptionEN: Two huge London sides go toe-to-toe at Stamford Bridge as Chelsea prepares for a huge end to the season with 4th place still to play for as well as the FA Cup final. The last time the Blues played Arsenal, the Gunners won 3-1.

events/strFilename: English Premier League 2021-05-13 Aston Villa vs Everton
events/strDescriptionEN: Everton faces a trip to Aston Villa in the Premier League. After avoiding relegation on the final day last year, The Villains have enjoyed a successful season and look set for a top half finish, for the first time since the 2010/2011 season.

events/strFilename: English Premier League 2021-05-13 Manchester United vs Liverpool
events/strDescriptionEN: Manchester United and Liverpool clash in the latest chapter of one of soccers greatest rivalries. A win against its bitter rival is vital for Liverpool as it looks to secure a place in next season’s UEFA Champions League.

events/strFilename: English Premier League 2021-05-14 Newcastle vs Manchester City
English Premier League 2021-05-15 Brighton vs West Ham
events/strDescriptionEN: Brighton and Hove Albion looks to disrupt West Ham United’s push for a top-four finish on the South Coast. The Hammers had to mount two comebacks to draw 2-2 when these two teams went head-to-head in East London.

events/strFilename: English Premier League 2021-05-15 Burnley vs Leeds
events/strDescriptionEN: Leeds United travels to Burnley where a win would help Marcelo Bielsa’s team solidify its place in the top half of the table. The Clarets form at Turf Moor has been poor over recent months, as their last win here came at the end of January.

events/strFilename: English Premier League 2021-05-15 Southampton vs Fulham
events/strDescriptionEN: Southampton hosts Fulham on the penultimate day of the season, with Fulham already relegated. It was a rather uneventful game when the Cottagers faced Southampton last December, the two teams played out a 0-0 draw on the banks of the River Thames.

events/strFilename: English Premier League 2021-05-16 Everton vs Sheffield United
events/strDescriptionEN: Everton takes on already-relegated Sheffield United in the Premier League. Carlo Ancelotti’s men from Merseyside are pushing for a place in the European spots, and will need to pick up three points here to stand any chance of qualification.

events/strFilename: English Premier League 2021-05-16 West Brom vs Liverpool
events/strDescriptionEN: Sam Allardyces West Bromwich Albion hosts Liverpool at the Hawthorns with the Baggies needing a win to maintain their Premier League status. When the two sides met at Anfield, Semi Ajayi scored a late equalizer in a 1-1 draw.

events/strFilename: English Premier League 2021-05-16 Tottenham vs Wolves
events/strDescriptionEN: Tottenham Hotspur welcomes Wolverhampton Wanderers to North London. There will be a huge focus on Wolves boss Nuno Espirito Santo, the Portuguese coach is being linked with the managerial vacancy at Spurs.

events/strFilename: English Premier League 2021-05-16 Crystal Palace vs Aston Villa
events/strDescriptionEN: Crystal Palace and Aston Villa square off with both teams in a much better position than 12 months ago. Already with their Premier League status confirmed, its now a case of securing the highest possible finish before attention turns to 2021/22.

events/strFilename: English Premier League 2021-05-18 Brighton vs Manchester City
events/strDescriptionEN: Brighton and Hove Albion welcomes Pep Guardiola’s Manchester City to the Amex. A dogged defensive display wasn’t enough for Brighton in the reverse fixture, where a Phil Foden strike helped City secure the win at Etihad Stadium.

events/strFilename: English Premier League 2021-05-18 Chelsea vs Leicester
events/strDescriptionEN: Leicester City and Chelsea clash in a game which could have major implications in the race for a top four finish. This is the second time in three days the two teams have gone head-to-head after facing each other in Saturday’s FA Cup Final.

events/strFilename: English Premier League 2021-05-18 Manchester United vs Fulham
events/strDescriptionEN: Relegated Fulham looks to salvage some pride against Manchester United at Old Trafford. Striker Edinson Cavani, who has recently signed a contract extension, scored during United’s 2-1 win at Craven Cottage last January.

events/strFilename: English Premier League 2021-05-18 Southampton vs Leeds
events/strDescriptionEN: Leeds United takes the long journey down to St. Mary’s, completing Southampton’s congested run of three games in the space of a week. The reverse fixture at Elland Road saw the Yorkshire side win comprehensively with a 3-0 victory.

events/strFilename: English Premier League 2021-05-19 Burnley vs Liverpool
events/strDescriptionEN: Turf Moor hosts its first fans of the campaign in Burnleys final home game of the season against Liverpool. The Reds still have a chance of qualifying for next seasons UEFA Champions League - a win will give a key boost before the final matchday.

events/strFilename: English Premier League 2021-05-19 Crystal Palace vs Arsenal
events/strDescriptionEN: Arsenal has come to loathe the sight of Crystal Palace, having not defeated the Eagles since 2018. Roy Hodgson has already assured Palace of top-flight football next year, but the Gooners must get a result as it strives for continental football.

events/strFilename: English Premier League 2021-05-19 Everton vs Wolves
events/strDescriptionEN: Evertons quest for European soccer continues as Carlo Ancelottis team hosts Wolverhampton Wanderers at Goodison Park. Michael Keanes powerful late header was the difference when the teams met earlier in the season in a 2-1 win.

events/strFilename: English Premier League 2021-05-19 Newcastle vs Sheffield United
events/strDescriptionEN: Sheffield United faces Newcastle United at St. James’ Park. A second half penalty from Blades legend Billy Sharp separated the two teams in the reverse fixture, will there a be a similar result in the North East?

events/strFilename: English Premier League 2021-05-19 Tottenham vs Aston Villa
events/strDescriptionEN: Aston Villa takes on Tottenham Hotspur in North London. While the UEFA Champions League is maybe a step too far for Spurs, they could still play European soccer next season by securing a place in the UEFA Europa League.

events/strFilename: English Premier League 2021-05-19 West Brom vs West Ham
events/strDescriptionEN: West Bromwich Albion plays its penultimate game in the Premier League against West Ham United before heading back to the EFL Championship. The Hammers UEFA Champions League ambitions are hanging by a thread after three defeats in their last five.

events/strFilename: English Premier League 2021-05-23 Arsenal vs Brighton
events/strDescriptionEN: Arsenal hosts Brighton and Hove Albion on the final day as fans make their long awaited return to Emirates Stadium. The Seagulls were victorious here 18 months ago and have a decent record against the Gunners in recent years.

events/strFilename: English Premier League 2021-05-23 Aston Villa vs Chelsea
events/strDescriptionEN: Chelsea plays its final game before next weeks UEFA Champions League final. Aston Villas England hopefuls have one final audition to make Gareth Southgates EURO squad, while the Blues will want to head into next weeks showpiece in winning form.

events/strFilename: English Premier League 2021-05-23 Fulham vs Newcastle
events/strDescriptionEN: Fulham welcomes Newcastle United to Craven Cottage for the final game of the Premier League season. Scott Parkers men have already been relegated after teams like Newcastle hit a purple patch of form to pull away at the back end of the season.

events/strFilename: English Premier League 2021-05-23 Leeds vs West Brom
events/strDescriptionEN: Leeds United will play in front of its fans for the first time this season, as West Brom turns up to Elland Road before returning to the EFL Championship next season. Leeds United won the reverse fixture 5-0 at the Hawthorns back in December.

events/strFilename: English Premier League 2021-05-23 Leicester vs Tottenham
events/strDescriptionEN: Leicester City could seal a place in next seasons Champions League with a win over Tottenham Hotspur on the final day. Foxes boss Brendan Rodgers has been linked with the vacant managers role at Spurs, could this be his final game with Leicester?

events/strFilename: English Premier League 2021-05-23 Liverpool vs Crystal Palace
events/strDescriptionEN: Liverpools challenging season reaches its climax at Anfield as former Reds boss Roy Hodgson leads Crystal Palace in what could be the final game of his managerial career. Hodgsons career began in Sweden in 1976 and spans over 1200 games to date.

events/strFilename: English Premier League 2021-05-23 Manchester City vs Everton
events/strDescriptionEN: Fernandinho and Sergio Aguero will lift the Premier League title together in front of fans, but not before Manchester Citys home clash with Everton at the Etihad. The Toffees are still in the running for the UEFA Europa League.

events/strFilename: English Premier League 2021-05-23 Sheffield United vs Burnley
events/strDescriptionEN: Sheffield United, headed back to the second tier of English football, welcomes Burnley to Bramall Lane for the last game of the season. When the two met at Turf Moor in December, it was captain Ben Mee whose goal was the difference between the teams.

events/strFilename: English Premier League 2021-05-23 West Ham vs Southampton
events/strDescriptionEN: With just one game left of the season, West Ham United takes on Southampton with all eyes on the Hammers European aspirations. Its been an unbelievable season for David Moyes men, but anything less than a win could have catastrophic consequences.

events/strFilename: English Premier League 2021-05-23 Wolves vs Manchester United
events/strDescriptionEN: One game out from the UEFA Europa League final, Manchester United heads to Wolverhampton Wanderers on the final day of the Premier League season. United have enjoyed an impressive campaign, finishing second under Ole Gunnar Solskjaer.
